main.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
main.name: Sauron, the Dark Lord
main.oracle_text:
Ward—Sacrifice a legendary artifact or legendary creature.
Whenever an opponent casts a spell, amass Orcs 1.
Whenever an Army you control deals combat damage to a player, the Ring tempts you.
Whenever the Ring tempts you, you may discard your hand. If you do, draw four cards.

card.name: Anger
card.oracle_text:
Haste
As long as Anger is in your graveyard and you control a Mountain, creatures you control have haste.
card.flavor_text:
"Molten earth has no anger of its own. Only by infusing it with your own rage can the magma seethe and take shape."
—Koth of the Hammer

card.name: Bone Miser
card.oracle_text:
Whenever you discard a creature card, create a 2/2 black Zombie creature token.
Whenever you discard a land card, add {B}{B}.
Whenever you discard a noncreature, nonland card, draw a card.

card.name: Wonder
card.oracle_text:
Flying
As long as Wonder is in your graveyard and you control an Island, creatures you control have flying.
card.flavor_text:
"The awestruck birds gazed at Wonder. Slowly, timidly, they rose into the air."
—*Scroll of Beginnings*

card.name: Vandalblast
card.oracle_text:
Destroy target artifact you don't control.
Overload {4}{R} (You may cast this spell for its overload cost. If you do, change "target" in its text to "each.")
card.flavor_text: Beauty is in the eye of the exploder.

card.name: Buried Alive
card.oracle_text: Search your library for up to three creature cards, put them into your graveyard, then shuffle.
card.flavor_text: The scrape of shovels and the tumble of cold dirt soon muffled their pleas.

card.name: Drowned Catacomb
card.oracle_text:
Drowned Catacomb enters tapped unless you control an Island or a Swamp.
{T}: Add {U} or {B}.

card.name: Bojuka Bog
card.oracle_text:
Bojuka Bog enters tapped.
When Bojuka Bog enters, exile target player's graveyard.
{T}: Add {B}.

card.name: Sulfur Falls
card.oracle_text:
Sulfur Falls enters tapped unless you control an Island or a Mountain.
{T}: Add {U} or {R}.
card.flavor_text:
"We have inherited the mysteries of the Thran, but few of the answers."
—Jhoira

card.name: Filth
card.oracle_text:
Swampwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Swamp.)
As long as Filth is in your graveyard and you control a Swamp, creatures you control have swampwalk.
card.flavor_text:
"As the portal closed, Filth oozed through. The stench of evil followed it in."
—*Scroll of Beginnings*

card.name: Urborg, Tomb of Yawgmoth
card.oracle_text: Each land is a Swamp in addition to its other land types.
card.flavor_text:
"Yawgmoth's corpse is a wound in the universe. His foul blood seeps out, infecting the land with his final curse."
—Lord Windgrace

card.name: Counterspell
card.oracle_text: Counter target spell.

card.name: Exotic Orchard
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add one mana of any color that a land an opponent controls could produce.
card.flavor_text:
"It was a strange morning. When we awoke, we found our trees transformed. We didn't know whether to water them or polish them."
—Pulan, Bant orchardist

card.name: Unearth
card.oracle_text:
Return target creature card with mana value 3 or less from your graveyard to the battlefield.
Cycling {2} ({2}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)
card.flavor_text: No matter how deep you bury it, some evil refuses to stay dead.

card.name: Extract from Darkness
card.oracle_text: Each player mills two cards. Then you put a creature card from a graveyard onto the battlefield under your control.
card.flavor_text: If you want to wreak havoc above, sometimes it's best to look below.

card.name: Arcane Signet
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity.
card.flavor_text: It started as a mere drop of water. The Magic Mirror crystallized it into much more.

card.name: Living Death
card.oracle_text: Each player exiles all creature cards from their graveyard, then sacrifices all creatures they control, then puts all cards they exiled this way onto the battlefield.

card.name: Command Tower
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity.
card.flavor_text:
"Approach my tower on bended knee or depart from it as ash upon the wind."
—Gadwick, the Wizened

card.name: Feed the Swarm
card.oracle_text: Destroy target creature or enchantment an opponent controls. You lose life equal to that permanent's mana value.
card.flavor_text:
"On vile wings and bloody wind, the swarm will rise."
—Skyclave inscription

card.name: Entomb
card.oracle_text: Search your library for a card, put that card into your graveyard, then shuffle.
card.flavor_text: A grave is the safest place to store ill-gotten treasures.

card.name: Black Sun's Twilight
card.oracle_text: Up to one target creature gets -X/-X until end of turn. If X is 5 or more, return a creature card with mana value X or less from your graveyard to the battlefield tapped.
card.flavor_text:
"Where once there was complacence, Sheoldred brought ambition, and soon the will of Yawgmoth reigned."
—Monument inscription

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Mount Doom
card.oracle_text:
{T}, Pay 1 life: Add {B} or {R}.
{1}{B}{R}, {T}: Mount Doom deals 1 damage to each opponent.
{5}{B}{R}, {T}, Sacrifice Mount Doom and a legendary artifact: Choose up to two creatures, then destroy the rest. Activate only as a sorcery.

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Gollum, Patient Plotter
card.oracle_text:
When Gollum, Patient Plotter leaves the battlefield, the Ring tempts you.
{B}, Sacrifice a creature: Return Gollum from your graveyard to your hand. Activate only as a sorcery.

card.name: Negate
card.oracle_text: Counter target noncreature spell.
card.flavor_text: Teferi gave them time. Karn gave them a chance. But it was Melira who paid the ultimate price to free Ajani from Phyrexia's grasp.

card.name: Sunken Hollow
card.oracle_text:
({T}: Add {U} or {B}.)
Sunken Hollow enters tapped unless you control two or more basic lands.
card.flavor_text: On the continent of Tazeem, rushing waters plunge through narrow canyons into mist-cloaked lakes.

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Call of the Ring
card.oracle_text:
At the beginning of your upkeep, the Ring tempts you.
Whenever you choose a creature as your Ring-bearer, you may pay 2 life. If you do, draw a card.
card.flavor_text: "The Ring is mine!"

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Bilbo, Retired Burglar
card.oracle_text:
When Bilbo, Retired Burglar enters or leaves the battlefield, the Ring tempts you.
Whenever Bilbo deals combat damage to a player, create a Treasure token.
card.flavor_text: "I don't know half of you half as well as I should like; and I like less than half of you half as well as you deserve."

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Witch-king of Angmar
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Whenever one or more creatures deal combat damage to you, each opponent sacrifices a creature of their choice that dealt combat damage to you this turn. The Ring tempts you.
Discard a card: Witch-king of Angmar gains indestructible until end of turn. Tap it.

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Barad-dûr
card.oracle_text:
Barad-dûr enters tapped unless you control a legendary creature.
{T}: Add {B}.
{X}{X}{B}, {T}: Amass Orcs X. Activate only if a creature died this turn.
card.flavor_text:
"Those who pass the gates of Barad-dûr do not return."
—Gandalf

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Saruman's Trickery
card.oracle_text:
Counter target spell.
Amass Orcs 1. (Put a +1/+1 counter on an Army you control. It's also an Orc. If you don't control an Army, create a 0/0 black Orc Army creature token first.)
card.flavor_text:
"I gave you the chance of aiding me willingly."
—Saruman

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Nazgûl
card.oracle_text:
Deathtouch
When Nazgûl enters, the Ring tempts you.
Whenever the Ring tempts you, put a +1/+1 counter on each Wraith you control.
A deck can have up to nine cards named Nazgûl.

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Ringsight
card.oracle_text: The Ring tempts you. Search your library for a card that shares a color with a legendary creature you control, reveal it, put it into your hand, then shuffle.
card.flavor_text: Frodo was able to see beneath their black wrappings. In their white faces burned keen and merciless eyes.

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: The Bath Song
card.oracle_text:
(As this Saga enters and after your draw step, add a lore counter. Sacrifice after III.)
I, II — Draw two cards, then discard a card.
III — Shuffle any number of target cards from your graveyard into your library. Add {U}{U}.

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Palantír of Orthanc
card.oracle_text: At the beginning of your end step, put an influence counter on Palantír of Orthanc and scry 2. Then target opponent may have you draw a card. If that player doesn't, you mill X cards, where X is the number of influence counters on Palantír of Orthanc, and that player loses life equal to the total mana value of those cards.

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Spiteful Banditry
card.oracle_text:
When Spiteful Banditry enters, it deals X damage to each creature.
Whenever one or more creatures your opponents control die, you create a Treasure token. This ability triggers only once each turn.
card.flavor_text:
"One ill turn deserves another."
—Saruman

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Ringwraiths
card.oracle_text:
When Ringwraiths enters, target creature an opponent controls gets -3/-3 until end of turn. If that creature is legendary, its controller loses 3 life.
When the Ring tempts you, return Ringwraiths from your graveyard to your hand.

card.name: Shinka, the Bloodsoaked Keep
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add {R}.
{R}, {T}: Target legendary creature gains first strike until end of turn.
card.flavor_text: The keep was called the Hornburg, for a trumpet sounded upon the tower echoed in the Deep behind, as if armies long-forgotten were issuing to war from caves beneath the hills.

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Claim the Precious
card.oracle_text: Destroy target creature. The Ring tempts you.
card.flavor_text:
"I think it is a sad story, and it might have happened to others, even to some Hobbits that I have known."
—Gandalf

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Birthday Escape
card.oracle_text: Draw a card. The Ring tempts you.
card.flavor_text: As Bilbo finished his speech, he slipped the ring on his finger, and he was never seen by any Hobbit in Hobbiton again.

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Orcish Medicine
card.oracle_text:
Target creature gains your choice of lifelink or indestructible until end of turn.
Amass Orcs 1. (Put a +1/+1 counter on an Army you control. It's also an Orc. If you don't control an Army, create a 0/0 black Orc Army creature token first.)

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Glorious Gale
card.oracle_text: Counter target creature spell. If it was a legendary spell, the Ring tempts you.
card.flavor_text: The Elves of Lórien took Dol Guldur. Galadriel threw down its walls and laid bare its pits, and the forest was cleansed.

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Sam's Desperate Rescue
card.oracle_text: Return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand. The Ring tempts you.
card.flavor_text: "By all the signs, there's a large warrior loose, with an Elf-sword, and an axe as well maybe." Gorbag spat. Sam smiled grimly at this description of himself.

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Inherited Envelope
card.oracle_text:
When Inherited Envelope enters, the Ring tempts you.
{T}: Add one mana of any color.
card.flavor_text:
"Keep it secret, and keep it safe!"
—Gandalf

card.set_name: The Lord of the Rings: Tales of Middle-earth
card.name: Sauron's Ransom
card.oracle_text: Choose an opponent. They look at the top four cards of your library and separate them into a face-down pile and a face-up pile. Put one pile into your hand and the other into your graveyard. The Ring tempts you.
card.flavor_text: "He was dear to you, I see. And now he shall endure the slow torment of years."

card.name: Lord of the Nazgûl
card.oracle_text:
Flying
Wraiths you control have protection from Ring-bearers.
Whenever you cast an instant or sorcery spell, create a 3/3 black Wraith creature token with menace. Then if you control nine or more Wraiths, Wraiths you control have base power and toughness 9/9 until end of turn.

card.oracle_text:
(As this Saga enters and after your draw step, add a lore counter. Sacrifice after IV.)
I, II, III — Create a 3/3 black Wraith creature token with menace. The Ring tempts you.
IV — For each opponent, gain control of up to one target creature that player controls until end of turn. Untap those creatures. They gain haste until end of turn. The Ring tempts you.

card.name: Relic of Sauron
card.oracle_text:
{T}: Add two mana in any combination of {U}, {B}, and/or {R}.
{3}, {T}: Draw two cards, then discard a card.
card.flavor_text: While the power of Sauron grew, light and living things forsook his borders.

card.name: The Black Gate
card.oracle_text:
As The Black Gate enters, you may pay 3 life. If you don't, it enters tapped.
{T}: Add {B}.
{1}{B}, {T}: Choose a player with the most life or tied for most life. Target creature can't be blocked by creatures that player controls this turn.

card.name: Fellwar Stone
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add one mana of any color that a land an opponent controls could produce.
card.flavor_text:
"What do you have that I cannot obtain?"
—Mairsil, the Pretender

card.name: Jet Medallion
card.oracle_text: Black spells you cast cost {1} less to cast.

card.name: Path of Ancestry
card.oracle_text:
Path of Ancestry enters tapped.
{T}: Add one mana of any color in your commander's color identity. When that mana is spent to cast a creature spell that shares a creature type with your commander, scry 1. (Look at the top card of your library. You may put that card on the bottom.)

card.name: Oversold Cemetery
card.oracle_text: At the beginning of your upkeep, if you have four or more creature cards in your graveyard, you may return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.
card.flavor_text:
"'Get out! Get out!' the dead screamed.
'We've not room for one more! Get out!'"
—*Hexes of Dunbarrow*

card.name: Arcane Denial
card.oracle_text:
Counter target spell. Its controller may draw up to two cards at the beginning of the next turn's upkeep.
You draw a card at the beginning of the next turn's upkeep.

card.name: Minas Morgul, Dark Fortress
card.oracle_text:
Minas Morgul, Dark Fortress enters tapped.
{T}: Add {B}.
{3}{B}, {T}: Put a shadow counter on target creature. For as long as that creature has a shadow counter on it, it's a Wraith in addition to its other types. (A creature with shadow can block or be blocked by only creatures with shadow.)

card.name: Dragonskull Summit
card.oracle_text:
Dragonskull Summit enters tapped unless you control a Swamp or a Mountain.
{T}: Add {B} or {R}.
card.flavor_text:
"You mean someone made all this? Dragons?"
—Sabalom Glitz

card.name: Darkwater Catacombs
card.flavor_text:
"They were placed, after death. These are tombs. Water tombs, some sort of fluid, anyway."
—The Twelfth Doctor

card.name: Shadowblood Ridge
card.flavor_text:
"Demons run when a good man goes to war. Night will fall and drown the sun, when a good man goes to war."
—River Song

card.name: Roaming Throne
card.oracle_text:
Ward {2}
As Roaming Throne enters, choose a creature type.
Roaming Throne is the chosen type in addition to its other types.
If a triggered ability of another creature you control of the chosen type triggers, it triggers an additional time.

card.name: Black Market Connections

card.name: Toxic Deluge
card.oracle_text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, pay X life.
All creatures get -X/-X until end of turn.
card.flavor_text:
"It's a difficult task to quarantine a plague that moves with the clouds."
—Esara, healer adept

card.name: Reanimate
card.oracle_text: Put target creature card from a graveyard onto the battlefield under your control. You lose life equal to its mana value.
card.flavor_text:
"You'd better be worth it."
—Liliana Vess

card.name: Smoldering Marsh
card.oracle_text:
({T}: Add {B} or {R}.)
Smoldering Marsh enters tapped unless you control two or more basic lands.
card.flavor_text: Even worse, the only toilet paper was locked in a nearby safe.

card.name: Faithless Looting
card.oracle_text:
Draw two cards, then discard two cards.
Flashback {2}{R} (You may cast this card from your graveyard for its flashback cost. Then exile it.)

card.name: Swiftfoot Boots

card.flavor_text:
"There is great wisdom in rushing headlong into combat . . . if you're prepared."
—Kenjek, captain of the Thousand Swords

Lands you control have "{T}: Add one mana of any color."
{T}: Add one mana of any color.
card.flavor_text: Dimir mages put the lanterns to good use, creating shapeshifters and sleeper agents from mana foreign to them.

card.name: Victimize
card.oracle_text: Choose two target creature cards in your graveyard. Sacrifice a creature. If you do, return the chosen cards to the battlefield tapped.
card.flavor_text:
"Die. But die knowing that your pathetic life will yield a great bounty for me."
—Zul Ashur, lich lord

card.name: Sol Ring
card.oracle_text: {T}: Add {C}{C}.
card.flavor_text: Lost to time is the artificer's art of trapping light from a distant star in a ring of purest gold.

card.name: Arena of Glory
card.oracle_text:
Arena of Glory enters tapped unless you control a Mountain.
{T}: Add {R}.
{R}, {T}, Exert Arena of Glory: Add {R}{R}. If that mana is spent on a creature spell, it gains haste until end of turn. (An exerted permanent won't untap during your next untap step.)

card.name: Coiling Rebirth
card.oracle_text:
Gift a card (You may promise an opponent a gift as you cast this spell. If you do, they draw a card before its other effects.)
Return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield. Then if the gift was promised and that creature isn't legendary, create a token that's a copy of that creature, except it's 1/1.

card.oracle_text: Destroy target creature or enchantment. You lose 2 life.
card.flavor_text: Each spindrell is the lingering consciousness of a survivor consumed by cellarspawn—a ragged, drifting remnant pulsing with constant psychic agony.

card.oracle_text: The owner of target permanent shuffles it into their library, then reveals the top card of their library. If it's a permanent card, they put it onto the battlefield.

card.name: Mask of Griselbrand
card.flavor_text: The legacy of evil lives on.

card.oracle_text:

card.oracle_text:

card.oracle_text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, discard a card.
Draw two cards.
card.flavor_text:
"Remember all the great heroes who were careful and never did anything risky? Me neither."
—Syr Carah, the Bold

card.oracle_text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, sacrifice a creature.
Search your library for a card, put that card into your hand, then shuffle.
card.flavor_text: Gix pierced his disciples' minds and savored their experiences as he took in their knowledge.
